Perry in Check if ability target type is "Point Target"?: GetAbilityTargetType() returns the type of units the ability targets, if it were a unit target. To check what kind of behavior it has (because that's what you want), you can use the following:
if bit.band(ability:GetBehavior(), DOTA_ABILITY_BEHAVIOR_UNIT_TARGET) ~= 0 then -- Unit target! end if (bit.band(ability:GetBehavior(), DOTA_ABILITY_BEHAVIOR_POINT) ~= 0 then -- Point target! end
Ofcourse if your ability has both behaviors at the same time, you just check if either target unit (ability:GetCursrotTarget()) or target position (ability:GetCursorPosition()) is not nil

H3katonkheir 03-Apr-19 11:00 PM
I'm trying to create an ability that blocks damage, down to a minimum post armour reduction. Seems easy enough with Lua, 'cept that the MODIFIER_PROPERTY_PHYSICAL_CONSTANT_BLOCK function always runs before 'OnAttacked' and 'OnTakeDamage' functions. Is there a way to edit the output damage on either 'OnAttacked' or 'OnTakeDamage' functions (or some other work around)? Setting up a global damage filter just for this seems extremely excessive.
Almouse 03-Apr-19 11:19 PM
our kv+lua solution:
"Modifiers" { "modifier_damage_block" { "Passive" "1" "IsPurgable" "0" "IsHidden" "1" "Properties" { "MODIFIER_PROPERTY_PHYSICAL_CONSTANT_BLOCK" "%damage_blocked" } "OnTakeDamage" { "RunScript" { "ScriptFile" "scripts/vscripts/abilities/common_damage_block.lua" "Function" "onTakeDamage" "Damage" "%attack_damage" "MinDamage" "%min_damage" } } } }
function onTakeDamage(keys) local caster = keys.caster local damage = keys.Damage local minDamage = keys.MinDamage if damage < minDamage then local hp_to_remove = CalculateDamage(keys.attacker, caster, minDamage) local health = caster:GetHealth() local newHealth = (health - hp_to_remove) if newHealth > 1 then caster:SetHealth(newHealth) else caster:Kill(keys.ability, keys.attacker) end end end
i'm actually not sure if or why it works, some parts of it look very fishy, but maybe you can try it (edited)
Nibuja 03-Apr-19 11:24 PM
I did something pretty similiar lua only some time ago, but I used MODIFIER_PROPERTY_INCOMING_DAMAGE_PERCENTAGE with a value of -100 instead. Should work if you want to modify the damage completly.

functions in lua are not "declared"
they are assigned

@FlamingCrossbow
------------- -- Ability -- ------------- -- lua Initialization stuff donate = class({}) LinkLuaModifier( "donated", "<path_to_this_file>", LUA_MODIFIER_MOTION_NONE ) -- OnSpellStart function donate:OnSpellStart() self.TARGET = self:GetCursorTarget() -- FireSound EmitSoundOn( "Donating", self.TARGET ) -- Apply Modifier self.TARGET:AddNewModifier( self:GetCaster(), -- player source self, -- ability source "donated", -- modifier name {} -- kv ) end -- OnChannelFinish function donate:OnChannelFinish( bInterrupted ) -- Remove modifier self.TARGET:RemoveModifierByName( "donated" ) end -------------- -- Modifier -- -------------- -- Lua initialization stuff donated = class({}) -- IsHidden function donated:IsHidden() return false end -- IsDebuff (also IsBuff) function donated:IsDebuff() return false end function donated:OnCreated( kv ) -- %interval local interval = self:GetAbility():GetSpecialValueFor( "interval" ) -- ThinkInterval self:StartIntervalThink( interval ) end -- OnIntervalThink function donated:OnIntervalThink() local TARGET = self:GetParent() -- GrantXPGold TARGET:ModifyGold( 10, --iGoldChange false, --bReliable DOTA_ModifyGold_Unspecified -- iReason ) end -- EffectName function donated:GetEffectName() return "particle_name" end -- EffectAttachType function donated:GetEffectAttachType() return PATTACH_ABSORIGIN_FOLLOW end
 (edited)
Most function have similar name from DD to Lua There will be few adjustments, but you'll get the hang of it in no time.
